PVR was originally referred to as '''massive vitreous retraction''' and then as '''massive periretinal proliferation'''. The name Proliferative vitreo retinopathy was provided in 1989 by the [[Silicone Oil Study group]]. The name is derived from ''proliferation'' (by the [[retinal pigment epithelium|retinal pigment epithelial]] and [[glial cell]]s) and ''vitreo retinopathy'' to include the tissues which are affected, namely the [[vitreous humor]] (or simply vitreous) and the [[retina]].<ref>
